description:
EL POLLO A LA BRASA
// Whole Chicken ($26.95) - 4 stars
The most redeeming quality of Limon's chicken was juiciness of its white meat - an indicator that the chicken was truly well-roasted. The aji sauces were interesting, although I'm still more of a ketchup and hot sauce kinda guy.

EL CEVICHE
// Ceviche Mixto ($15.95 + $2.50 taro chips) - 3 stars
The ceviche did not come with taro chips, so we placed a side order to enjoy the extra crunch. I thought that the fish itself could have been softer, and the shrimp was just alright.

SMALL HOT PLATES
// Lengua ($12.95) - 5 stars
My favorite dish of the night! The beef tongue was melt-in-your-mouth tender. If you enjoy lengua, you have to try this one out.

// Carne a la Parrilla ($18.95) - 4 stars
Although the skirt steak was tough to chew, I liked the red wine demi glaze.

SIDES
// Yuca Fries - 5 stars
// Camote Frito (Sweet Potato Fries) - 4 stars
